-- UAW sets Wednesday deadline
-- 
-- Mon Oct 8, 2007 11:36am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/10/08/us-chrysler-uaw-deadline-idUSN0832066420071008

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - The United Auto Workers union has set a Wednesday deadline for reaching a new labor agreement with Chrysler LLC and has threatened to strike the automaker if a deal is not reached by that time. 

 The UAW, which has been in high-level talks with the No. 3 U.S. automaker since Friday, set a "strike target deadline" of 11 a.m. EDT on Wednesday, Chrysler spokeswoman Michele Tinson said on Monday. (Reporting by  Kevin Krolicki )